verses.verse: The <S%H3068>Lord<s%> <S%H4427>reigns<s%>, he is <S%H3847>clothed<s%> with <S%H1348>majesty<s%>; the <S%H3068>Lord<s%> is <S%H3847>clothed<s%> with <S%H5797>strength<s%>, with which he has <S%H247>girded<s%> <S%H8398>himself<s%>: the world also is <S%H3559>stablished<s%>, that it cannot be <S%H4131>moved<s%>.
Your <S%H3678>throne<s%> is <S%H3559>established<s%> of <S%H227>old<s%>: you are from <S%H5769>everlasting<s%>.

The <S%H5104>floods<s%> have lifted <S%H5375>up<s%>, O <S%H3068>Lord<s%>, the <S%H5104>floods<s%> have lifted <S%H5375>up<s%> their <S%H6963>voice<s%>; the <S%H5104>floods<s%> lift <S%H5375>up<s%> their <S%H1796>waves<s%>.

The <S%H3068>Lord<s%> on <S%H4791>high<s%> is <S%H117>mightier<s%> than the <S%H6963>noise<s%> of <S%H7227>many<s%> <S%H4325>waters<s%>, <S%H117>Yes<s%>, than the mighty <S%H4867>waves<s%> of the <S%H3220>sea<s%>.
